general_exclusion_criteria:
History of clinically significant pulmonary toxicity or interstitial lung disease/pneumonitis;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease (heart failure NYHA class III-IV, recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina);
Significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin > 1.5× ULN or AST/ALT > 3× ULN) or severe renal dysfunction (creatinine clearance ≤30 mL/min);
Active central nervous system metastases causing symptoms or requiring steroids (>10 mg prednisone equivalent daily);
Known human immunodeficiency virus infection, chronic hepatitis B or C infections;
Concurrent serious opportunistic infection or unresolved acute infection;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
ECOG/Karnofsky performance status greater than 1 (poor functional status);
Use of prohibited concomitant medications (strong CYP enzyme modulators) or participation in another interventional clinical trial.

