Residual non‑hematologic toxicities greater than Grade 1 (excluding alopecia) from prior anticancer therapy;
Receipt of gemtuzumab ozogamicin (Mylotarg) or other agents associated with heightened risk of hepatic sinusoidal obstruction syndrome/vveno‑occlusive disease;
Extramedullary disease located in immune‑privileged sites such as central nervous system, testes, or eyes;
History of myocardial infarction within the preceding two years;
Venous thromboembolism (deep vein thrombosis or pulmonary embolus) within the preceding one year (unless line‑associated deep vein thrombosis resolved and off anticoagulation);
Stroke or transient ischemic attack within the preceding one year;
Clinically significant gastrointestinal hemorrhage, peptic ulcer disease, erosive gastritis, intestinal perforation, or hemoptysis within six months;
Previous episode of thrombotic microangiopathy, hemolytic‑uremic syndrome, or thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura;
Severe allergic reaction to intravenous iron preparations or murine‑derived monoclonal antibodies;
Presence of clinically significant donor‑specific antibodies in the prospective recipient;
Inability to discontinue concomitant medicines that strongly affect cytochrome P450 pathways responsible for cyclophosphamide or thiotepa metabolism during the designated peri‑transplant interval;
Active uncontrolled bacterial, viral, or fungal infection;
Any prior allogeneic or autologous hematopoietic stem cell transplantation;
Prior solid organ transplantation;
Medical conditions or prior radiation exposure prohibiting delivery of myeloablative total‑body irradiation (total myeloid and lymphoid irradiation);
Human immunodeficiency virus infection while on combination antiretroviral therapy;
Seropositivity for chronic hepatitis B or hepatitis C viruses;
Significant psychiatric disorder or unstable social situation compromising adherence to study procedures;
Pregnancy or lactation (women of child‑bearing potential must have a documented negative pregnancy test before enrolment);
History of another malignant neoplasm, except when disease‑free for at least five years or when the prior cancer was limited to cervix intraepithelial neoplasia, basal cell carcinoma, or cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma diagnosed and treated within the last five years.

