History of pneumonitis;
Congestive heart failure or left ventricular systolic impairment;
Long QT syndrome or corrected QT interval ≥470 milliseconds;
Cardiac dysfunction (shortening fraction <27%);
Uncontrolled hypertension;
Severe hepatic dysfunction (bilirubin >1.5× ULN, ALT >3× ULN);
Renal dysfunction (creatinine clearance <70 ml/min/1.73 m²);
Poor performance status (Karnofsky <50 for age >16 yr or Lansky <50 for age ≤16 yr);
Active central nervous system infection or uncontrolled systemic infection;
Human immunodeficiency virus infection, chronic hepatitis B or C infection, or other significant immunocompromising condition;
Auto‑immune disease requiring systemic cytotoxic/immunosuppressive therapy;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Inability or unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Recent (<72 hours) use of strong CYP3A4/5 inhibitor or recent (<2 weeks) use of strong CYP3A4/5 inducer;
Concurrent receipt of other anticancer investigational agents;
Evidence of widespread disseminated disease (unless covered by special cohort permitting leptomeningeal spread);
Additional active malignancy requiring treatment within past 3 years.

