Active or history of pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease, pulmonary fibrosis requiring systemic steroids, or imaging findings suggesting ILD/pneumonitis;
Diagnosis of immunodeficiency or active autoimmune disease needing chronic systemic corticosteroids (>10 mg/day prednisolone-equivalent) or other immunosuppression within the past 2 years;
Sensory peripheral neuropathy grade ≥ 2 (applies to Part 2);
Clinically significant ongoing gastrointestinal disease (e.g., inflammatory bowel disease, severe ulcers, recent major bleed);
Recent major surgery or radiation therapy ≤4 weeks before enrolment or radiation involving >30 % bone marrow;
Known hypersensitivity to any investigational product components (PF‑07985045, gemcitabine, nab‑paclitaxel, cetuximab, bevacizumab, FOLFOX, 5‑FU, pembrolizumab, sasanlimab, cisplatin, carboplatin, pemetrexed, SHP2 inhibitors);
Baseline hematologic laboratory abnormalities;
Renal insufficiency;
Hepatic dysfunction.

