History of other active malignant neoplasm within the past three years (exceptions: adequately treated basal cell/carcinoma of skin, superficial urothelial carcinoma, in‑situ disease);
Active or prior interstitial lung disease, pulmonary fibrosis, or grade ≥2 pneumonitis;
Clinically active or symptomatic central nervous system metastases, spinal cord compression, or leptomeningeal disease (treated, asymptomatic cases permissible under strict criteria);
Unstable or symptomatic cardiovascular disease—including myocardial infarction within six months, New York Heart Association Class II–IV heart failure, uncontrolled angina, atrial fibrillation/flutter or other arrhythmias requiring medication, left ventricular ejection fraction < 50 %; prolonged corrected QT interval exceeding gender‑specific thresholds;
Severe uncontrolled arterial hypertension (systolic > 180 mm Hg or diastolic > 110 mm Hg);
Chronic systemic glucocorticoid usage greater than 10 mg daily prednisone equivalents or any other immunosuppressive therapy;
Significant ocular pathology such as corneal disease affecting vision;
Pregnancy, lactation, or inadequate contraception in women of child‑bearing potential, and inability to meet contraceptive requirements in men;
Known human immunodeficiency virus infection that is not virologically suppressed;
Active hepatitis B or C infection not appropriately managed per protocol specifications.

