Uncontrolled inter‑current illnesses—including active infection, symptomatic congestive heart failure, unstable angina, serious cardiac arrhythmia, or major psychiatric disorder limiting compliance;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Evidence of myelodysplastic syndrome or cytogenetic changes suggestive of myelodysplasia;
Active hepatitis B or C infection confirmed by positive PCR;
